President Donald Trump issued a statement to the Congress of the United States informing them of the death of George H.W. Bush, the forty-first President of the United States. Trump praised Bush's selfless work for justice and peace, especially during his service in World War Two and his efforts to bring an end to the Cold War. He highlighted Bush's courage and adventurous spirit, noting that he had jumped from an aircraft in celebration of his accomplishments. Trump concluded by stating that Bush's example will continue to inspire future generations.